 Mock Interview :

Q1. What is Node.js, and how does it differ from traditional server-side environments like Apache?

Q2. What are the main advantages of using Node.js for backend development?

Q3. Explain the concept of callback functions in Node.js and why they are important in asynchronous programming.

Q4. Name some of the core modules available in Node.js without requiring external installation.

Q5. How would you use the fs module to read a file asynchronously in Node.js?

Q6. Describe the purpose of the http module in Node.js. Provide an example of creating an HTTP server.

Q7. What is npm (Node Package Manager), and why is it important for Node.js development?

Q8. Name a few popular third-party npm packages used for web development.

Q9. How do you install and manage third-party packages using npm in a Node.js project?

Q10. Discuss the advantages and potential risks of using third-party npm packages in a production environment.

Q11. Describe the role of the package.json file in a Node.js project.